        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 9:22PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 921 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southeast of Riverview, or 15 miles southeast of Brewton,
moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Baker.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
